# Directory layout (baseline)

Adapt subfolders under `playbooks/`, `vars/`, `rulebooks/`, `templates/`, and `files/` to the scenario, but keep this spine:

```
aap-demo-<slug>/
├── ansible.cfg.example
├── inventory.yml
├── vault.yml.example
├── README.md
├── .gitignore                         # must include entries below
├── opencode.json                      # wires .agents/rules/*.mdc into OpenCode's instructions
├── .agents/rules/
│   ├── artifact--casc.mdc              # CasC standards (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--casc-playbooks.mdc    # aap_config/aap_cleanup recipe (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--layout.mdc            # directory layout (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--ansible-quality.mdc   # Ansible/YAML quality (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--roles.mdc             # role standards (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--readme.mdc            # README style (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--status-badge.mdc      # Status badge as first README badge (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--code-comments.mdc     # playbook/task/CasC comments (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--demo-deployment-modes.mdc # lab/dev vs customer/PoC mode flag (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--checklist.mdc         # pre-handoff checklist (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--self-sufficiency.mdc  # dependency/dual-mode standards (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--testing-log.mdc       # docs/testing.md session workflow (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--vault-naming.mdc      # vault.yml.example conventions (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--demo-variables.mdc    # demo_variables.yml.example conventions (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--git-repository.mdc    # Git repository config block (alwaysApply true)
│   ├── artifact--execution-environment.mdc # custom EE build/CasC pattern (alwaysApply true)
│   └── all--english-content.mdc        # English-only prose and comments (alwaysApply true)
├── .cursor/rules -> .agents/rules/     # symlink, for Cursor rule discovery
├── collections/
│   └── requirements.yml
├── group_vars/all/
│   ├── demo_variables.yml.example
│   ├── organizations.yml
│   ├── projects.yml
│   ├── credentials.yml
│   ├── inventories.yml
│   ├── job_templates.yml
│   ├── workflow_templates.yml
│   └── ...                            # further CasC files as needed
├── vars/
├── playbooks/
│   ├── aap_config.yml
│   ├── aap_cleanup.yml
│   ├── site.yml                       # optional data-plane entry if needed
│   ├── verify.yml                     # idempotency / smoke tests
│   └── setup/                         # optional ordered setup (e.g. 01_..., 02_...)
├── rulebooks/                         # only if EDA is in scope
├── roles/                             # optional host automation
├── context/
│   └── execution-environment.yml      # optional: custom EE when cloud SDKs needed
├── docs/
│   ├── setup.md
│   ├── procedures.md
│   ├── verification.md
│   └── testing.md                     # session-start status log, see artifact--testing-log.mdc
├── templates/
└── files/
```

## Cross-tool rule wiring

`.agents/rules/` is the single source of truth for the artifact's standards. Do not fork rule bodies per tool:

- **Cursor** only discovers *rules* from `.cursor/rules/` (it does read *skills* directly from `.agents/skills/`, but not rules). Symlink it: `ln -s ../.agents/rules .cursor/rules` (relative, so it survives the artifact being moved or exported).
- **OpenCode** does not have a Cursor-style glob/alwaysApply rule engine; it loads plain instruction files instead. Ship a minimal `opencode.json` at the artifact root:

  ```json
  {
    "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
    "plugin": [
      "opencode-cursor-rules@1.0.1"
    ]
  }
  ```

  This loads every rule body into context on every session (OpenCode does not distinguish `alwaysApply` from `globs` — treat this as acceptable since all `artifact--*` copies use `alwaysApply: true`).

## `.gitignore` baseline entries

Every artifact **`.gitignore`** must include at least:

```
vault.yml
group_vars/all/demo_variables.yml
collections/ansible_collections/
*.retry
__pycache__/
*.pyc
ansible.cfg
.ansible/
```

When the artifact includes a **`context/`** directory for Execution Environment builds, also add:

```
context/_build/
context/files/
context/context/
```
